Key Match Events: Jake Bauers hit an RBI single in the ninth inning, giving the Milwaukee Brewers a 2-1 victory over the Philadelphia Phillies.
Milwaukee closer Devin Williams struck out Alec Bohm, Bryson Stott, and Brandon Marsh in order in the ninth inning.
Rhys Hoskins hit his 25th home run in the fifth inning to tie the game.
Alec Bohm gave Philadelphia a 1-0 lead in the second inning with his first home run since August 15.
Post-Match Reflections: Jake Bauers commented on the intensity of the game and the team's determination to win despite already clinching the division.
Willy Adames expressed pride in proving doubters wrong and hoped the team could win it all.
Philadelphia manager Rob Thomson reflected on the tight, low-scoring nature of the game and the disappointment of losing.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Milwaukee Brewers clinched their second straight division title and made the playoffs for the sixth time in the last seven seasons.
The Brewers are chasing the Phillies and Dodgers for the National League's two first-round playoff byes.
Freddy Peralta made his career-high 31st start of the season, allowing one run on two hits in five innings.
Philadelphia starter Aaron Nola went seven innings, allowing one run on three hits while striking out nine and walking one.
